news.title: Citigroup takes 4.20 lakh sq ft space in Chennai and Pune
news.para: "The Leadership in Energy and Environmental Design (LEED) certified incremental spaces, spread across 4.20 lakh sq ft at the existing locations at DLF Cybercity Chennai and EON IT Park, Pune would augment the capacity to serve global client of Citi," a company statement said here.

news.title: I-T takes over Mehul Choksi's assets in first Benami law confiscation
news.para: The assets linked to Choksi were provisionally attached last year under the BTPA after a probe by the Mumbai IT investigation wing ascertained that the assets were benami with Choksi being the ultimate beneficiary owner.

news.title: UP metro to appoint consultant for monetisation of 86-acre land in Lucknow
news.para: UPMRC is a special purpose vehicle (SPV) set up by the Uttar Pradesh government and the central government as a joint venture. It operates metro trains in Lucknow and Kanpur.

news.title: DLF found guilty of denying benefit of input tax credit to buyers
news.para: The National Anti-Profiteering Authority (NAA) held that DLF denied the benefit of input tax credit to the buyers of the apartments and the upcoming shops in its projects in Gurgaon--The Camellias, The Crest and The Ultima.

news.title: Fitch withdraws ratings on debt-laden China Evergrande, subsidiaries
news.para: The rating agency in December downgraded Evergrande and its subsidiaries, Hengda Real Estate Group Co Ltd and Tianji Holding Ltd, to so-called "restricted default" status, saying the firms had defaulted on their offshore bond obligations.

news.title: Stanza Living enters into managed apartments business with $10 million investment
news.para: In a statement, Stanza said, it has expanded product portfolio by launching customised, fully-managed apartments in six cities across the country, including Delhi, NCR (Gurugram), Bengaluru, Hyderabad, Pune and Chennai.

news.title: Ultratech Cement to invest Rs 12,886 crore for capacity expansion by FY25
news.para: The company plans to increase its capacity by 22.6 metric tonnes per annum (mtpa) from the current grey cement capacity of 119.95 mtpa.

news.title: ABIL chairman allegedly received 'kickbacks' to facilitate loans from DHFL: CBI
news.para: ​​The CBI has stumbled upon two payments of over Rs 68.8 crore and Rs 292 crore to arrested ABIL chairman Avinash Bhosale's companies made by Radius Developers, whose owner Sanjay Chhabaria was recently arrested in the case, they said.

news.title: HC refuses nod to ex-chairman of Mantri Realty to go to Nepal; takes note of risk of not returning
news.para: ​Sunil Mantri, who is accused of defaulting on loans amounting to Rs 300 crore, sought permission to travel to Nepal from June 2 to 8. Mantri's firms are under liquidation after he failed to return the Rs 300 crore to the creditors.

news.title: Drones to map all land parcels in Secunderabad cantonment board under Svamitva scheme
news.para: CEO Ajith Reddy said that it is aimed at establishing clear ownership of property in inhabited areas by mapping land parcels using drones and providing ‘Record of Rights’ to every household with issuance of legal ownership cards.

news.title: West Bengal: Trust properties, estates set for rent revision, Rs 10 crore target in 2022-23
news.para: The office has been entrusted with hundreds of prime properties in Kolkata and rest of the state as well as parcels of land and buildings in other states by the Calcutta High Court by way of the Official Trustees Act, 1913, or the Administrator General Act, 1963.

news.title: Sipcot to create a land bank of 45,000 acre in Tamil Nadu in five years
news.para: So far, the agency has identified little over 31,000 acres of land. Of this, around 6,000 acres of land have been acquired and close to 8,000 acres of land are in various stages of acquisition.

news.title: Kerala: Number of illegally issued land titles may cross 600
news.para: On the basis of a hearing conducted in six out of the eight villages under the Devikulam taluk where such ‘pattayam’ have been issued, at least 30 more such illegal ‘pattayam’ have been newly identified.

news.title: Two-month rebate on property taxes yields Chandigarh civic body Rs 46.57 crore
news.para: The received amount is quite significant for the authority, especially as the civic body has estimated Rs 80 crore from the property tax collection for the current financial year.

news.title: Punjab National Bank raises benchmark lending rate by 0.15%
news.para: The revision follows an off-cycle rate increase by the Reserve Bank in May. The central bank hiked the repo rate -- at which it lends short-term money to banks -- by 0.40 per cent to 4.40 per cent.
